  <page>
    <title>Biconditional introduction</title>
    <id>4286</id>
    <revision>
      <id>401720371</id>
      <timestamp>2010-12-11T03:25:20Z</timestamp>
      <contributor>
        <ip>99.69.132.75</ip>
      </contributor>
      <text xml:space="preserve">{{Rules of inference}}
In [[mathematical logic]], '''biconditional introduction''' is the [[rule of inference]] that, if B follows from A, and A follows from B, then A [[if and only if]] B.

For example, from the statements &quot;if I'm breathing, then I'm alive&quot; and &quot;if I'm alive, then I'm breathing&quot;, it can be inferred that &quot;I'm breathing if and only if I'm alive&quot;.

Formally, biconditional introduction is the rule schema.

:&lt;math&gt; A \to B \, &lt;/math&gt;
:&lt;math&gt; \underline{B \to A} &lt;/math&gt;
:&lt;math&gt; A \leftrightarrow B &lt;/math&gt;

==See also==

*[[Logical biconditional]]

{{DEFAULTSORT:Biconditional Introduction}}
[[Category:Logic]]
[[Category:Rules of inference]]

[[eo:Dukondiĉa enkonduko]]</text>
    </revision>
  </page>
  <page>
    <title>Biconditional elimination</title>
    <id>4287</id>
    <revision>
      <id>430909477</id>
      <timestamp>2011-05-25T21:06:43Z</timestamp>
      <contributor>
        <username>Rich Farmbrough</username>
        <id>82835</id>
      </contributor>
      <minor />
      <comment>Minor fixes using [[Project:AWB|AWB]]</comment>
      <text xml:space="preserve">{{Unreferenced|date=May 2011}}{{Rules of inference}}
'''Biconditional elimination''' allows one to infer a [[Material conditional|conditional]] from a biconditional: if ( A ↔ B ) is true, then one may infer either direction of the biconditional, ( A → B ) and ( B → A ).

For example, if it's true that I'm breathing [[if and only if]] I'm alive, then it's true that if I'm breathing, I'm alive; likewise, it's true that if I'm alive, I'm breathing.

Formally:

  &lt;u&gt;( A ↔ B )&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;
  ∴ ( A → B )

also

  &lt;u&gt;( A ↔ B )&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;
  ∴ ( B → A )

==See also==

*[[Logical biconditional]]
*[[If and only if]]

